# Basic Linux Commands

###  Print current work directory
`$ pwd`

### Check current user
`$ whoami`

### List files and directories with details
`$ ls -l`


### Show IP address
`$ show addr show`
or
`$ ip a `

### Show memory details
`$ free -m`

#### Show mounted file systems
`$ df -h`

###  print out a file text or config file
`$ cat /etc/hosts`

### Show mounted filesystems like a tree 
`findmnt`


